# {{lb|en|Ireland|New England|idiomatic|archaic}} A generic [[greeting]] said to someone in the [[morning]].

====Usage notes====
This term should be considered [[apocryphal]] of Irish speech is a [[stereotype]]. While popularly used in the United States when imitating Irish people, or when celebrating one's Irish heritage (e.g. on St. Patrick's day), native Hiberno-English speakers would never use this phrase. See [[Hollywood Irish]].

